1
00:00:03,100 --> 00:00:06,330
Concert Band Competition

2
00:00:06,330 --> 00:00:07,460
Hurry!

3
00:00:10,840 --> 00:00:12,500
Gosh, I'm so nervous...

4
00:00:13,480 --> 00:00:16,340
Kyoto Concert Band Competition

5
00:00:13,480 --> 00:00:16,340
Kansai Concert Band Competition

6
00:00:13,480 --> 00:00:16,340
Kyoto Preliminary

7
00:00:14,280 --> 00:00:15,280
Here it comes!

8
00:00:21,050 --> 00:00:21,850
Gold!

9
00:00:22,120 --> 00:00:23,850
We got gold!

10
00:00:23,850 --> 00:00:25,750
I'm going to go tell Asami.

11
00:00:25,750 --> 00:00:28,520
She's so nervous, she's hiding in the washroom.

12
00:00:30,260 --> 00:00:33,460
The following schools will compete in the Kansai Competition.

13
00:00:40,440 --> 00:00:41,330
Gold...

14
00:00:45,370 --> 00:00:47,500
We got dud gold, but still gold.

15
00:00:53,820 --> 00:00:55,220
Kousaka-san?

16
00:00:56,050 --> 00:00:57,850
You're happy enough to cry, huh?

17
00:00:59,190 --> 00:01:01,420
Congratulations, we got gold.

18
00:01:04,530 --> 00:01:05,860
I'm so upset...

19
00:01:07,060 --> 00:01:08,760
I'm so upset, I could die.

20
00:01:09,960 --> 00:01:12,760
Why are people happy, when we didn't even make it?

21
00:01:12,870 --> 00:01:15,600
Weren't we shooting for the Nationals?

22
00:01:17,840 --> 00:01:20,470
Did you really think we could make the Nationals?

23
00:01:24,610 --> 00:01:26,670
Aren't you upset?

24
00:01:28,820 --> 00:01:30,050
I'm upset!

25
00:01:30,650 --> 00:01:32,210
I'm totally upset!

26
00:01:56,140 --> 00:02:00,010
Why did I believe the rumor that my breasts would get bigger,

27
00:02:00,010 --> 00:02:02,640
once I was in high school?

28
00:02:03,820 --> 00:02:05,090
I'm off.

29
00:02:05,090 --> 00:02:06,320
Take care.

30
00:02:08,860 --> 00:02:10,920
When my high school life began,

31
00:02:11,690 --> 00:02:15,560
that was the kind of thing
I was thinking about.

32
00:02:25,240 --> 00:02:27,380
Entrance Ceremony

33
00:02:26,210 --> 00:02:30,310
Although there weren't many people from my middle school here,

34
00:02:27,380 --> 00:02:31,380
Baseball Club

35
00:02:27,380 --> 00:02:31,380
Congratulations on

36
00:02:27,380 --> 00:02:31,380
your admissions!

37
00:02:30,680 --> 00:02:34,550
this school was the only one with the sailor-style uniforms I'd always liked,

38
00:02:34,550 --> 00:02:37,750
and because, in a lot of ways,
I wanted a fresh start.

39
00:02:38,490 --> 00:02:40,220
Attention, new students!

40
00:02:40,220 --> 00:02:42,050
Welcome to Kitauji High School.

41
00:02:44,130 --> 00:02:45,290
It's the concert band.

42
00:02:45,660 --> 00:02:48,860
To celebrate your admittance...

43
00:03:20,300 --> 00:03:21,490
They're hopeless.

44
00:05:00,230 --> 00:05:01,630
They suck!

45
00:05:03,500 --> 00:05:04,970
They don't play together.

46
00:05:05,500 --> 00:05:07,660
They're off-pitch and out of rhythm.

47
00:05:08,500 --> 00:05:13,130
But well, I guess they aren't trying for Nationals...

48
00:05:18,180 --> 00:05:20,480
But they really sucked.

49
00:05:21,150 --> 00:05:21,880
What sucked?

50
00:05:22,520 --> 00:05:23,140
Huh?

51
00:05:23,580 --> 00:05:26,650
You said, "They really sucked."

52
00:05:27,860 --> 00:05:29,190
Did I say that out loud?

53
00:05:29,960 --> 00:05:30,980
Wait...

54
00:05:31,760 --> 00:05:32,860
Who are you?

55
00:05:32,860 --> 00:05:33,900
Me?

56
00:05:33,900 --> 00:05:35,200
Hazuki Katou!

57
00:05:35,200 --> 00:05:36,820
I sit behind you. Nice to meet you.

58
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:39,490
I'm Kumiko Oumae.

59
00:05:39,870 --> 00:05:40,840
Nice to meet you.

60
00:05:40,840 --> 00:05:42,300
So, what-

61
00:05:42,700 --> 00:05:43,870
Take your seats!

62
00:05:45,040 --> 00:05:48,240
You're in high school now.
You shouldn't make noise in class.

63
00:05:48,240 --> 00:05:50,340
I'm unimpressed.

64
00:05:51,710 --> 00:05:53,380
Explain the length of your skirts.

65
00:05:54,180 --> 00:05:55,180
Fix them now.

66
00:05:55,180 --> 00:05:56,380
Sorry.

67
00:05:59,490 --> 00:06:01,690
I'll be in charge of class 1-3.

68
00:06:01,690 --> 00:06:03,220
My name is Michie Matsumoto.

69
00:06:01,690 --> 00:06:05,650
Michie Matsumoto

70
00:06:03,590 --> 00:06:05,650
First, I'll call the roll.

71
00:06:06,730 --> 00:06:08,060
Yuudai Asai.

72
00:06:08,060 --> 00:06:08,690
Here.

73
00:06:09,930 --> 00:06:11,230
Yuki Ishikawa.

74
00:06:11,230 --> 00:06:11,930
Here.

75
00:06:12,830 --> 00:06:14,400
Hiroko Uchiyamada.

76
00:06:14,400 --> 00:06:15,170
Here.

77
00:06:16,070 --> 00:06:17,610
Yoko Eguchi.

78
00:06:17,610 --> 00:06:18,370
Here.

79
00:06:19,040 --> 00:06:20,610
Kumiko Oumae.

80
00:06:20,610 --> 00:06:21,370
Here.

81
00:06:22,110 --> 00:06:23,340
Hazuki Katou.

82
00:06:23,340 --> 00:06:24,310
Here.

83
00:06:25,750 --> 00:06:27,080
Ryokuki...

84
00:06:27,880 --> 00:06:29,280
Kawashima?

85
00:06:29,280 --> 00:06:33,860
Sorry, it's "Sapphire."

86
00:06:33,860 --> 00:06:36,590
Written as "green" and "shining."

87
00:06:37,130 --> 00:06:40,190
Sapphire Kawashima...

88
00:06:40,190 --> 00:06:41,560
Sapphire, huh?

89
00:06:41,560 --> 00:06:42,760
I'm sorry.

90
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:43,300
That sounds awesome.

91
00:06:42,760 --> 00:06:44,060
I won't make that error again.

92
00:06:45,600 --> 00:06:47,260
It's fine.

93
00:06:48,440 --> 00:06:50,270
Kumiko, let's walk home together.

94
00:06:50,270 --> 00:06:51,860
Huh? "Kumiko"?

95
00:06:52,140 --> 00:06:54,540
Yeah, isn't that your name?

96
00:06:54,740 --> 00:06:57,150
Yeah, it is.

97
00:06:57,150 --> 00:06:58,200
Right?

98
00:06:58,480 --> 00:07:00,080
I'm Hazuki!

99
00:07:00,080 --> 00:07:01,450
You can call me "Katou."

100
00:07:01,450 --> 00:07:02,420
Call me whatever.

101
00:07:02,420 --> 00:07:04,080
Don't you walk home with anyone else?

102
00:07:04,520 --> 00:07:05,110
No.

103
00:07:05,450 --> 00:07:08,620
I decided I'm going to make new friends in high school

104
00:07:08,620 --> 00:07:11,060
and do all kinds of new things.

105
00:07:11,430 --> 00:07:13,450
I'm counting on you, Kumiko-chan!

106
00:07:15,460 --> 00:07:19,230
Episode 1

107
00:07:15,460 --> 00:07:19,230
Welcome to High School

108
00:07:19,430 --> 00:07:21,340
So what sucked?

109
00:07:21,340 --> 00:07:22,700
Let's just forget that.

110
00:07:24,040 --> 00:07:25,900
Opal-chan!

111
00:07:26,140 --> 00:07:28,780
No, it's something greener.

112
00:07:28,780 --> 00:07:29,740
Hey...

113
00:07:29,740 --> 00:07:32,910
Hey, isn't that Tuba-kun?

114
00:07:32,910 --> 00:07:33,750
Huh?

115
00:07:34,780 --> 00:07:36,720
It's so cute, Tuba-kun.

116
00:07:36,720 --> 00:07:38,410
I love it.

117
00:07:39,090 --> 00:07:40,920
- Could I touch-
- Hey, Opal-chan.

118
00:07:41,260 --> 00:07:42,360
It's "Sapphire."

119
00:07:42,360 --> 00:07:45,130
Oh, sorry. Sapphire-chan...

120
00:07:45,130 --> 00:07:46,190
You like it?

121
00:07:46,190 --> 00:07:48,830
Yes! It's so cute...

122
00:07:48,830 --> 00:07:49,460
What is it?

123
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:51,320
It's a tuba mascot character.

124
00:07:52,500 --> 00:07:53,300
Tuba?

125
00:07:53,570 --> 00:07:55,140
It's a brass instrument.

126
00:07:55,140 --> 00:07:57,140
A brass instrument?

127
00:07:57,140 --> 00:08:00,470
Midori was in the concert band, on contrabass.

128
00:08:00,840 --> 00:08:01,810
Contrabass?

129
00:08:01,810 --> 00:08:02,640
Midori?

130
00:08:03,080 --> 00:08:05,710
Midori is my name.

131
00:08:06,650 --> 00:08:09,420
You know, the name "Sapphire" is kind of...

132
00:08:09,420 --> 00:08:13,690
Sapphire

133
00:08:09,820 --> 00:08:13,690
I'd appreciate if you'd call me "Midori."

134
00:08:14,190 --> 00:08:17,730
And "contrabass" is the name of an instrument.

135
00:08:17,730 --> 00:08:19,860
This huge thing!

136
00:08:19,860 --> 00:08:22,100
It's like a freakish violin.

137
00:08:22,100 --> 00:08:23,120
Have you seen one?

138
00:08:23,460 --> 00:08:24,830
I've seen one.

139
00:08:24,830 --> 00:08:26,000
You have?

140
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:27,570
I was in concert band, too.

141
00:08:27,570 --> 00:08:28,900
Really?

142
00:08:28,900 --> 00:08:30,770
Um...

143
00:08:31,040 --> 00:08:32,510
Oh, Kumiko Oumae.

144
00:08:32,840 --> 00:08:33,880
Call her "Kumiko."

145
00:08:33,880 --> 00:08:36,180
I'm Hazuki. Nice to meet you.

146
00:08:36,180 --> 00:08:37,350
Copy.

147
00:08:37,350 --> 00:08:38,680
What about you?

148
00:08:38,680 --> 00:08:40,620
What part did you play?

149
00:08:40,620 --> 00:08:41,850
Oh, baritone.

150
00:08:41,850 --> 00:08:43,350
I used to play euph.

151
00:08:43,350 --> 00:08:45,290
Yeah, I can see that.

152
00:08:45,290 --> 00:08:46,850
H-Huh? UFO?

153
00:08:46,850 --> 00:08:48,960
Not "UFO." It's "euph."

154
00:08:48,960 --> 00:08:50,790
It's called a euphonium.

155
00:08:51,430 --> 00:08:53,030
It's a smaller one of these.

156
00:08:53,030 --> 00:08:55,390
Yeah? That's really small.

157
00:08:56,760 --> 00:09:00,200
Until now, I've been in the tennis club.

158
00:09:00,200 --> 00:09:02,570
But with high school,
I might join the concert band.

159
00:09:03,440 --> 00:09:04,510
No way.

160
00:09:04,510 --> 00:09:07,130
I was about to go watch the concert band.

161
00:09:07,540 --> 00:09:10,610
How about we all go together?

162
00:09:10,610 --> 00:09:12,610
Welcome to the Concert Band

163
00:09:11,280 --> 00:09:13,110
Whoa, crazy!

164
00:09:13,110 --> 00:09:14,820
That's a trumpet, isn't it?

165
00:09:14,820 --> 00:09:16,880
I like those.

166
00:09:17,290 --> 00:09:19,190
They look awesome!

167
00:09:19,190 --> 00:09:21,620
Look, Hazuki-chan. That's a euph.

168
00:09:21,960 --> 00:09:22,860
Let's see.

169
00:09:22,860 --> 00:09:24,290
Huh, UFOs are huge!

170
00:09:24,760 --> 00:09:30,000
Jeez, you surprised me, Kumiko.
You said it was smaller than Tuba-kun...

171
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:31,870
Oh, sorry.

172
00:09:31,870 --> 00:09:33,200
Sax is nice, too!

173
00:09:37,570 --> 00:09:38,740
H-Hazuki-chan...

174
00:09:38,410 --> 00:09:39,270
Ow.

175
00:09:39,270 --> 00:09:40,270
Are you all right?

176
00:09:40,270 --> 00:09:41,570
What's this?

177
00:09:42,280 --> 00:09:45,710
Are you here to watch?

178
00:09:45,710 --> 00:09:47,580
Then, come in.

179
00:09:47,580 --> 00:09:49,350
Come on, join us!

180
00:09:50,420 --> 00:09:51,350
Gosh,

181
00:09:51,920 --> 00:09:53,150
she's pretty!

182
00:09:54,590 --> 00:09:57,750
Now, this is our school band.

183
00:09:58,260 --> 00:10:00,420
You're the first visitors.

184
00:10:00,900 --> 00:10:02,730
In commemoration, I'll give you candy.

185
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:05,170
Thank you.

186
00:10:06,600 --> 00:10:07,430
Huh?

187
00:10:15,210 --> 00:10:16,610
Asuka...

188
00:10:16,610 --> 00:10:17,140
Yes?

189
00:10:17,510 --> 00:10:19,910
We agreed not to talk to the new students too much,

190
00:10:19,910 --> 00:10:22,980
so we don't scare them, remember?

191
00:10:22,980 --> 00:10:24,120
Huh?

192
00:10:24,120 --> 00:10:25,850
They're already terrified.

193
00:10:26,150 --> 00:10:28,560
Sorry, make yourselves at home.

194
00:10:28,560 --> 00:10:29,920
Nice to meet you!

195
00:10:30,220 --> 00:10:31,190
Come on, let's go.

196
00:10:34,600 --> 00:10:36,060
Bronze Prize

197
00:10:34,600 --> 00:10:36,060
Kitauji Prefectural High School

198
00:10:34,900 --> 00:10:36,060
Bronze prize.

199
00:10:40,700 --> 00:10:43,370
Hey, what's that square thing?

200
00:10:43,370 --> 00:10:45,040
That's a tuner.

201
00:10:45,040 --> 00:10:46,670
You tune against it.

202
00:10:46,670 --> 00:10:47,540
Yeah?

203
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:50,640
Oh? Are you a beginner?

204
00:10:51,650 --> 00:10:52,310
Yes.

205
00:10:52,310 --> 00:10:53,550
I see!

206
00:10:53,550 --> 00:10:56,580
Then I'll teach you the basics of brass.

207
00:10:55,020 --> 00:10:56,580
Asuka...

208
00:10:57,080 --> 00:10:58,380
Fine, fine.

209
00:11:02,720 --> 00:11:04,390
A tuning B-flat, please.

210
00:11:12,530 --> 00:11:14,500
Trombone, place your note.

211
00:11:15,240 --> 00:11:17,970
Horn, you're off. Listen carefully.

212
00:11:21,180 --> 00:11:22,640
Let's do it again.

213
00:11:23,280 --> 00:11:25,050
You can use your tuner.

214
00:11:25,050 --> 00:11:25,910
What?

215
00:11:26,550 --> 00:11:28,310
They were a bit off.

216
00:11:28,950 --> 00:11:29,970
Really?

217
00:11:37,220 --> 00:11:38,490
Kousaka-san?

218
00:11:43,660 --> 00:11:44,650
Excuse me.

219
00:11:45,530 --> 00:11:46,830
Are you here to visit?

220
00:11:47,130 --> 00:11:49,800
No, I'd like to join.

221
00:11:52,570 --> 00:11:53,310
Really?

222
00:11:53,310 --> 00:11:55,310
Welcome to the concert band!

223
00:11:55,310 --> 00:11:57,040
Hurry, register her for the club!

224
00:11:57,040 --> 00:11:58,080
Now?

225
00:11:58,080 --> 00:11:59,450
Obviously.

226
00:11:59,450 --> 00:12:00,920
What if she runs away?

227
00:12:00,920 --> 00:12:02,550
She isn't a cat or anything.

228
00:12:01,820 --> 00:12:03,540
Maybe we should get going.

229
00:12:05,190 --> 00:12:06,880
Thank you!

230
00:12:10,730 --> 00:12:13,630
That girl was pretty.

231
00:12:13,630 --> 00:12:14,960
Do you know her?

232
00:12:14,960 --> 00:12:17,300
Huh? Well, it's more like

233
00:12:17,300 --> 00:12:19,700
I was with her in the middle school band.

234
00:12:19,970 --> 00:12:21,270
Then you know her.

235
00:12:21,770 --> 00:12:23,570
Not too well.

236
00:12:23,570 --> 00:12:25,230
That's it, huh?

237
00:12:34,580 --> 00:12:40,580
But the band here wasn't, uh...

238
00:12:42,560 --> 00:12:44,160
...as good as I expected.

239
00:12:44,160 --> 00:12:45,730
Really?

240
00:12:45,730 --> 00:12:47,790
That's right...

241
00:12:48,130 --> 00:12:51,630
They're probably aiming for a Prefectural silver.

242
00:12:51,630 --> 00:12:53,730
Silver would be pretty good, wouldn't it?

243
00:12:54,940 --> 00:12:58,810
If we wanted to go to the Kansai
Competition or to the Nationals,

244
00:12:58,810 --> 00:13:01,880
we'd have to get gold in each competition.

245
00:13:01,880 --> 00:13:05,150
And it can't be a dud gold.
It has to be a proper gold.

246
00:13:05,150 --> 00:13:08,180
Dud what? What's dud gold mean?

247
00:13:07,550 --> 00:13:12,990
School Band

248
00:13:07,550 --> 00:13:12,990
All experience levels welcome!

249
00:13:07,550 --> 00:13:12,990
Especially boys!

250
00:13:08,180 --> 00:13:12,350
Band competitions have gold, silver, and bronze prizes.

251
00:13:12,350 --> 00:13:15,120
Representatives are chosen from the gold-prize winners,

252
00:13:15,120 --> 00:13:17,630
and the ones not chosen are called "dud golds."

253
00:13:17,630 --> 00:13:20,800
Like Sapphire-chan said, if you want to move on to the next competition,

254
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:22,600
you can't have a dud gold...

255
00:13:21,500 --> 00:13:24,900
Phys-Ed

256
00:13:23,160 --> 00:13:24,900
Was that complicated?

257
00:13:24,900 --> 00:13:25,830
Yeah.

258
00:13:25,830 --> 00:13:26,770
Sorry.

259
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:31,040
But maybe if the three of us join, we can be their saviors.

260
00:13:31,040 --> 00:13:32,710
It isn't that simple.

261
00:13:32,710 --> 00:13:33,540
No?

262
00:13:33,540 --> 00:13:35,140
I'll do it.

263
00:13:35,140 --> 00:13:36,670
I love music.

264
00:13:38,250 --> 00:13:42,880
Music speaks to people's hearts, all throughout the world.

265
00:13:42,880 --> 00:13:45,510
I believe it's a powerful language.

266
00:13:48,590 --> 00:13:51,460
The signal isn't changing, is it?

267
00:13:52,230 --> 00:13:54,750
I forgot to press the button!

268
00:13:55,860 --> 00:13:58,030
Come on, Sapphire-chan...

269
00:13:58,030 --> 00:13:59,330
It's "Midori."

270
00:14:00,570 --> 00:14:01,700
Tap

271
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:03,630
How about you, Kumiko?

272
00:14:03,900 --> 00:14:04,960
How about it?

273
00:14:05,710 --> 00:14:06,870
The band?

274
00:14:06,870 --> 00:14:08,000
Me?

275
00:14:08,540 --> 00:14:10,170
I'm...

276
00:14:11,950 --> 00:14:14,180
I'm not sure.

277
00:14:16,250 --> 00:14:18,190
My train's here.

278
00:14:18,190 --> 00:14:20,020
I'm going this way.

279
00:14:20,020 --> 00:14:20,890
Bye.

280
00:14:20,890 --> 00:14:22,120
See you tomorrow.

281
00:14:26,590 --> 00:14:28,360
Oh, I get it now.

282
00:14:28,730 --> 00:14:31,490
When you said they sucked, you meant the band.

283
00:14:47,110 --> 00:14:48,910
Why?

284
00:14:50,550 --> 00:14:53,040
Kousaka-san was there...

285
00:14:55,060 --> 00:14:56,390
She's really good.

286
00:14:56,390 --> 00:15:00,050
I thought she'd be at Rakushu or Rikka or somewhere.

287
00:15:02,200 --> 00:15:03,760
Damn it...

288
00:15:04,270 --> 00:15:05,230
What?

289
00:15:08,740 --> 00:15:09,530
Hey.

290
00:15:10,140 --> 00:15:11,230
Oh, Shuichi.

291
00:15:12,610 --> 00:15:13,230
Huh?

292
00:15:13,870 --> 00:15:17,240
We've known each other since we were little. At least say hi.

293
00:15:17,240 --> 00:15:19,210
We're in the same school.

294
00:15:20,780 --> 00:15:22,080
You're tying your hair back?

295
00:15:22,080 --> 00:15:23,520
I guess...

296
00:15:23,520 --> 00:15:25,690
Oh yeah, I saw Reina Kousaka.

297
00:15:25,690 --> 00:15:27,320
I didn't know.

298
00:15:27,320 --> 00:15:30,380
Though, aren't you a bit slow?

299
00:15:30,790 --> 00:15:34,400
You told me not to talk to you, so I'm not talking to you.

300
00:15:34,400 --> 00:15:35,400
Huh?

301
00:15:35,400 --> 00:15:38,870
In the third year of junior high, you said, "Quit talking to me, ugly."

302
00:15:38,870 --> 00:15:41,940
Oh, that was because you asked me,

303
00:15:41,940 --> 00:15:44,410
"Are you eating at my place tonight?" in front of others.

304
00:15:44,410 --> 00:15:47,170
That's not right, and I don't really have time for this.

305
00:15:47,170 --> 00:15:47,880
Hey.

306
00:15:47,880 --> 00:15:49,240
Sorry, I'm going home.

307
00:15:50,740 --> 00:15:52,910
Hey, what are you doing about clubs?

308
00:15:54,980 --> 00:15:56,580
I haven't decided yet.

309
00:15:57,080 --> 00:15:58,110
Not band?

310
00:15:58,490 --> 00:15:59,450
What about you?

311
00:15:59,450 --> 00:16:00,110
Me?

312
00:16:00,520 --> 00:16:03,260
Well, it isn't like there's anything else I want to do.

313
00:16:03,260 --> 00:16:04,860
Band, I guess...

314
00:16:04,860 --> 00:16:05,520
Oh.

315
00:16:09,960 --> 00:16:11,300
I'm...

316
00:16:13,130 --> 00:16:14,120
I'm not joining.

317
00:16:14,570 --> 00:16:15,540
Huh?

318
00:16:15,540 --> 00:16:17,970
I was thinking of joining, but I decided not to.

319
00:16:17,970 --> 00:16:18,840
Why?

320
00:16:18,840 --> 00:16:19,770
Because.

321
00:16:19,770 --> 00:16:20,670
Bye.

322
00:16:23,340 --> 00:16:24,750
What the...

323
00:16:24,750 --> 00:16:26,840
I'm home.

324
00:16:28,220 --> 00:16:29,480
Oh, welcome home.

325
00:16:29,480 --> 00:16:30,880
How was high school?

326
00:16:30,880 --> 00:16:32,890
Hmm... Meh.

327
00:16:32,890 --> 00:16:34,660
Your sister's home.

328
00:16:34,660 --> 00:16:35,520
Yeah?

329
00:16:35,520 --> 00:16:37,420
Help me fix dinner.

330
00:16:37,420 --> 00:16:39,090
Okay.

331
00:16:52,210 --> 00:16:53,870
Band, huh?

332
00:16:55,910 --> 00:16:58,380
Did you really think we could make the Nationals?

333
00:17:06,520 --> 00:17:08,920
I didn't mean that in a bad way.

334
00:17:08,920 --> 00:17:12,890
I just kind of blurted out what I was thinking.

335
00:17:12,890 --> 00:17:16,100
And I was sort of happy that we got gold...

336
00:17:16,100 --> 00:17:18,230
Dud gold is still a gold-

337
00:17:18,230 --> 00:17:19,790
What are you doing?

338
00:17:20,070 --> 00:17:22,840
You even wore a ponytail.

339
00:17:22,840 --> 00:17:24,670
You're trying too hard on your first day.

340
00:17:24,940 --> 00:17:26,070
Shut up.

341
00:17:26,070 --> 00:17:27,910
And don't open the door without asking.

342
00:17:27,910 --> 00:17:28,810
Fine, fine.

343
00:17:28,810 --> 00:17:29,940
Sorry.

344
00:17:33,610 --> 00:17:34,520
Oh, yeah.

345
00:17:34,520 --> 00:17:36,520
I said, "Don't open it"!

346
00:17:36,520 --> 00:17:38,780
Are you quitting concert band?

347
00:17:39,620 --> 00:17:40,420
Why?

348
00:17:40,950 --> 00:17:41,820
Why?

349
00:17:42,220 --> 00:17:43,250
Because you're at Kitauji.

350
00:17:48,600 --> 00:17:50,890
Quitting, huh?

